As an independent entrepreneur who is introverted and values their privacy, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here's the advertisement: Follow the algorithm, share your personal charm. Get verified on that service, stay online 24/7, answer questions using your own video, and respond immediately. Video, video, and more video.
1/3
This year is a year of transformation for me.
I don't want to give my money, data, and energy to large tech companies anymore, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only offer a single, one-size-fits-all extroverted solution to everyone. I'm exploring new business models and trying to overcome my long-held idea that success can only be achieved by doing things in a certain way.
Good luck to me!
First step already taken.
I quit FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and unregistered my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, feeling great.
Recently, I subscribed to a European CRM service to better support GDPR, and I will migrate my business to it in the coming weeks.
I moved my MX records to Proton, and now I have a full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
